item.title: Ok my first attempt to make a model ice cream
item.dc:creator: @thathomonoob thathomonoob
item.description:
@thathomonoob wrote:

djspanke:

you guys, you’re dicks. for a first model, this is quite good, you’re gettong the hang of mating and putting things together, and next time, you can use primatives, just try making some of your own shapes=)

thanks[quote=“wayzey, post:20, topic:278999”][quote author=thathomonoob link=topic=368237.msg2791877#msg2791877 date=1242830738]

It’s so realistic!
Whoa 20 Minutes, something containing 3 unedited primitives usually takes hours!

i cant tell if ur making fun of me or not lol
[/quote]

I’m just messing so i’m making fun of you but not in a harsh way.

Really though I made a really crappy katana on my first try, did I post it though? Second attempt I made my first real model which was my lightsaber. Choose an object like a specific sword, get a picture of it. Then in metaseq load it as top image. Then using the create tool with ‘line’ and ‘both’ selected trace out your model. Then just follow a few tuts and mess around with the options till you get used to things and yer get good at it. Oh and follow Silent CJ’s tut, he explains all the options that are in metaseq, how to use them and what they are for (well for most options).[/quote]
ok
